    "Robinson published the first volume of the <em>Sylloge Nummorum Graecorum</em> for the British Academy in 1931, the corpus of Greek coinage.": [],
    "The volume with its detailed photographs, set the standard for the rest of the corpus.": [],
    "In 1933, Robinson and <a href=\"/mattinglyh\">Harold Mattingly</a> published the landmark <em>The Date of the Roman Denarius</em> effectively redating the coinage of Republican Rome.": [],
    "Robinson became Deputy Keeper of the Department 1936.": [],
    "There he worked closely with the Keeper, <a href=\"/hillg\">George Francis Hill</a>.": [],
    "Robinson was appointed Reader in Numismatics at Oxford, succeeding Joseph Grafton Milne (1867-1951) in 1938.": [],
    "He succeeded Hill as Keeper of the Department in 1949, a position he held until 1952.": [],
    "During this time, he was approached by the art collector Calouste Gulbenkian (1869 - 1955) to advise him on his acquisitions.": [
